=09A=
 fashion emergency :: Before COVID-19, Rent the Runway was on a 10-year =
=E2=80=9Crocket-ship growth path,=E2=80=9D building the =E2=80=9Ccloset in =
the cloud=E2=80=9D for its many customers. As the virus disrupted China=
=E2=80=99s fashion supply chains in January, the company quickly sought to =
mitigate inventory shortages. By mid-March, inventory had arrived, but shel=
ter-in-place orders were enacted, decimating Rent the Runway=E2=80=99s dema=
nd. Faced with no revenue and many fixed costs, Hyman had to act swiftly to=
 save the company she founded, slashing costs and making difficult people d=
ecisions. =E2=80=9CIt was a traumatic eight-day experience,=E2=80=9D she sa=
id. =E2=80=9CI had to do everything possible to not only save the business =
but to save the passion and the work of the thousands of people who=
=E2=80=99ve partnered with me over the last decade to build this industry-l=
eading company.=E2=80=9D

=09Alter your view :: In the past, employees =
came to work at the fast-growing company expecting to manage lots of succes=
sful projects and to rise in their roles and responsibilities quickly. When=
 the business changed almost overnight, Hyman had to reframe how employees =
saw their jobs in order to prevent mass attrition and motivate them through=
 the crisis. =E2=80=9CI had to convince people that their jobs were to lear=
n how to connect emotionally with folks on their team, how to inspire peopl=
e around them, how to ruthlessly prioritize what they=E2=80=99re working on=
, how to figure out how to do more with less.=E2=80=9D She championed the i=
dea of resilient leadership and emphasized that every employee is responsib=
le for it.=20

=09Address the existential questions :: Faced with an exis=
tential crisis, Hyman and her team asked themselves two essential questions=
 that guided their strategy during COVID-19 and provided an outlook for a p=
ost-pandemic future:=20

=09=09Will your business still be relevant after=
 COVID-19? The whole world is suffering from the same crisis at the same ti=
me, and this is fundamentally changing our values, how we live and how we w=
ork. =E2=80=9CThese trends are not necessarily going away.=E2=80=9D After p=
ondering the question, Hyman determined that Rent the Runway still had a pl=
ace in a post-COVID-19 world. =E2=80=9CYes, I think creating a sharing econ=
omy in a closet in the cloud is still relevant.=E2=80=9D

=09=09Coming =
out of COVID-19, will your business be more relevant or less relevant than =
