<h1><span style=3D"font-s=
ize:22px;"><span style=3D"font-family:georgia,serif;">Trevor Noah</span></s=
pan></h1>

<p><strong><span style=3D"font-size:16px;">Comedian and Host=
, <em>The Daily Show</em></span></strong></p>

<p><em style=3D"font-siz=
e: 14px;">Trevor Noah brought his nuanced perspective to the Summit, as he =
shared with members how his team has sustained the creative process in voic=
ing complex issues to a global audience.&nbsp;<br>
<br>
<a href=3D"http=
s://go.world50.com/e/159871/s-IN50-2H-2020-Trevor-Noah-mp3/fxrhdz/726796847=
?h=3DApKy5JNrNS6dqK3e1n0ULGMJM0Pf2HO1Y_10GXefBRU"><img alt=3D"" border=3D"0=
" height=3D"30" src=3D"https://go.world50.com/l/159871/2020-04-23/dm5ljd/15=
9871/114975/audio_player.jpg" style=3D"width: 140px; height: 30px; border-w=
idth: 0px; border-style: solid;" width=3D"140"></a></em></p>

<ul>
=
=09<li><strong>Finding the levity ::&nbsp;</strong>As the creators of a com=
edic news program,&nbsp;<em>The Daily Show</em>=E2=80=99s team is tasked wi=
th the daunting challenge of finding moments of levity within often-depress=
ing news stories. =E2=80=9CWe call it our =E2=80=98giggle at the funeral.=
=E2=80=99 We=E2=80=99re not laughing at the dead body, but there=E2=80=
=99s got to be a moment at the funeral where someone makes a joke and then =
we go, =E2=80=98Oh yeah, we=E2=80=99re still celebrating life.=E2=80=99=
=E2=80=9D The team stays focused on keeping the show=E2=80=99s perspective =
intact despite all that=E2=80=99s happening in the world. =E2=80=9CThat per=
spective is,=E2=80=9D said Noah, =E2=80=9Cthat contrary to popular belief, =
the world is not ending. And so, until the world ends, we can enjoy being h=
uman beings and still pay attention to everything going on around us.=
=E2=80=9D</li>
=09<li><strong>Make a new show ::</strong>&nbsp;When COVID=
-19 hit,&nbsp;<em>The Daily Show</em>=E2=80=99s creative team had to determ=
ine how to produce the program remotely and what it would look like without=
 a studio audience. Rather than focusing on the absence of his normal audie=
nce, Noah chose to get into the mindset that he was making a new show from =
his new reality. =E2=80=9CThat=E2=80=99s what I=E2=80=99ve tried to do: wor=
k within my reality.=E2=80=9D He even renamed the show&nbsp;<em>The Daily S=
ocial Distancing Show</em>&nbsp;as a reminder: =E2=80=9Cso that I, myself, =
would always remember that this is a specific thing that I=E2=80=99m doing =
because life is not normal.=E2=80=9D A member later echoed Noah=E2=80=99s c=
omments about leading through this crisis, saying, =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re a=
ll making new shows, so to speak.=E2=80=9D=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=
=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B</li>
=09<li><strong>Fueled by fire starters :=
:&nbsp;</strong>Asked what inspires his creativity, Noah emphasized the imp=
ortance of being surrounded by funny, creative people. When he=E2=80=99s fe=
eling uninspired, someone around him will inevitably say something that set=
s off =E2=80=9Can avalanche=E2=80=9D of jokes and humor, which reignites th=
e creative spark. =E2=80=9CAll I keep trying to do is make sure the group h=
as enough people in it who are fire starters, enough people who aren=
=E2=80=99t afraid to spark a joke, spark an idea, get something going.=
=E2=80=9D The team=E2=80=99s witty, intelligent conversations inform the sh=
ow=E2=80=99s conversational format. =E2=80=9CThe show is a conversation tha=
t is going on with the audience, so we try to maintain that energy througho=
ut.=E2=80=9D</li>
=09<li><strong>Everybody is your customer ::&nbsp;</str=
ong>When Noah arrived at&nbsp;<em>The Daily Show,</em>&nbsp;he focused on c=
hanging the show=E2=80=99s distribution because he realized that people=
=E2=80=99s viewing habits were gradually shifting. He put the show=E2=80=
=99s content on all platforms=E2=80=94from Snapchat and TikTok to YouTube a=
nd Instagram=E2=80=94to meet audiences where they are and to draw in new vi=
ewers. He also made sure the show engaged viewers through the linear TV pla=
tform but also sought to engage people who don=E2=80=99t watch TV at all. =
=E2=80=9CThat=E2=80=99s almost part of your customer base, even if they=
=E2=80=99re not your customer,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CEverybody can be =
a customer; they just aren=E2=80=99t right now.=E2=80=9D&nbsp;</li>
=09<l=
i><strong>The formula for comedy ::&nbsp;</strong>Comedy has a formula: tra=
gedy plus time, said Noah. =E2=80=9CAs long as you have enough time that se=
parates you enough from the tragedy, no matter how small or big it is, you=
=E2=80=99ll be able to laugh at it. The issue is right now we live in a wor=
ld where the tragedy is ongoing.=E2=80=9D People don=E2=80=99t know what to=
 laugh at anymore because they have no distance from the tragic reality. =
=E2=80=9CThey cannot laugh at the absurdity because the absurd has become t=
he real. That=E2=80=99s a very strange place to be in.=E2=80=9D He observed=
 that in more relaxed times, comedy tends to become much edgier, but in edg=
ier times, comedy has to be =E2=80=9Cmore of a soothing balm so people can =
get through their day.=E2=80=9D</li>
=09<li><strong>Empowering through te=
ch ::</strong>&nbsp;Recalling the life-changing day in his childhood when h=
is mother brought home a computer, Noah said, =E2=80=9CI was just learning =
the command prompts, but the world was infinite.=E2=80=9D Having experience=
d how empowering access to technology can be, Noah launched the Trevor Noah=
 Foundation in South Africa, which seeks to equip schools to reach their fu=
ll potential by providing the resources, equipment and training they need. =
=E2=80=9CSometimes people create technology for what they need, not for wha=
t the people they=E2=80=99re giving it to need,=E2=80=9D he said. Thus, the=
 foundation works with its partner Microsoft to bring tech to each school t=
hrough a human-centered design method that focuses on the school=E2=80=
=99s specific needs. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m trying to get to a place where =
=E2=80=A6 every school is connected, every student is connected and hopeful=
ly everyone has an equal
shot at a good education.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ul>=

